Setup:
  Must be called first and be passed the name of the program or project
Fatal
  This is a fatal call and exits the program gracfully.
Fatalf
  This is a fatal call and exits the progrma gracfully. But also can be passed a formatted string.
    ex:
      cli.Fatalf("Error: %s", foo)
Warn:
  This is a warning call and dosn't exit
Warnf:
  This is a warning call and dosn't exit. But can also be passed a formatted string.
    ex:
      cli.Warnf("Warn: %s", bar)
Debug:
  This is a debug call and is nice for debbuging your program. It is passed a debug tag and a debug value
    ex:
      cli.Debug("baz", foobar)
